han Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀππειραῖον\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀππειραῖον\">Α..ΕΙΡΑΙΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of I.Segesta\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Two horizontal strokes are visible, forming the upper part of two letters, such as Γ or Ε\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Nenci described the fragment as part of an architrave, but Ampolo and Erdas consider it more likely to be part of a statue base. Appeiraios is attested as the third onomastic element in the name of Diodoros son of Tittelos in \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001106\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001106\u003C/a>. This is likely to be another honorific, but not of course necessarily for the same individual.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 45.1393 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Nenci 1995 1183 no.2 tav.267.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001415\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001415\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Nenci 1997 1191-1192 tav.234.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001729\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001729\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> De Vido 2003 400 no.12 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002041\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002041\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Dubois 2008 87 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000160\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000160\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ampolo and Erdas 2019 G27 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>The letters are somewhat worn, but present a regular and wide/square module, broadly and deeply incised. Alpha with straight bar, epsilon with shorter middle bar, omicron smaller and above the line, rho with a small closed eye.\u003C/p> Line 1  13-17 (13 = omicron)  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[259,262,265,268,271,274,277,280],{"id":260,"html":261},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=